   257‚Üí * permitting calling it with or without a catch-all handler function.
   258‚Üí *
   259‚Üí * By default, TS-Pattern will throw an error if a runtime value isn't handled.
   261‚Üítype Exhaustive<output, inferredOutput> = {
   262‚Üí  /**
   263‚Üí   * `.exhaustive()` checks that all cases are handled, and returns the result value.
   264‚Üí   *
   265‚Üí   * If you get a `NonExhaustiveError`, it means that you aren't handling
   266‚Üí   * all cases. You should probably add another `.with(...)` clause
   267‚Üí   * to match the missing case and prevent runtime errors.
   268‚Üí   *
   269‚Üí   * [Read the documentation for `.exhaustive()` on GitHub](https://github.com/gvergnaud/ts-pattern#exhaustive)
   270‚Üí   *
   271‚Üí   */
