helpers.ts
     6‚Üí * ### LeastUpperBound
     7‚Üí * An interesting one. A type taking two imbricated sets and returning the
     8‚Üí * smallest one.
     9‚Üí * We need that because sometimes the pattern's inferred type holds more
    10‚Üí * information than the value on which we are matching (if the value is any
    11‚Üí * or unknown for instance).
    14‚Üíexport type LeastUpperBound<a, b> = b extends a ? b : a extends b ? a : never;
   180‚Üí * GuardValue returns the value guarded by a type guard function.
   182‚Üíexport type GuardValue<fn> = fn extends (value: any) => value is infer b
   183‚Üí  ? b
   184‚Üí  : fn extends (value: infer a) => unknown
   185‚Üí  ? a
   186‚Üí  : never;
